    "intro": "Deuteronomy 18 is a chapter with three interlocking movements, each answering the same underlying question: through what authorized channel does Yahweh speak to His people in the land? Interpretation must resist reading the movements independently. The priestly provision (vv. 1-8), the occult prohibition (vv. 9-14), and the prophetic promise (vv. 15-22) are a single unified argument about authorized mediation. The movements below trace that argument as Moses intends it, culminating in the chapter's Messianic climax and the canon of prophetic discernment that guards it.",
